New Records: Ben Stokes and Chris Woakes combined in an England-record stand to rescue their team from 192 for 6 to 339 for 9.
Key Match Events: Moeen Ali took 3 wickets for 42 runs.
Adil Rashid took 3 wickets for 54 runs.
Paul van Meekeren was stumped by Jos Buttler off Moeen Ali's bowling.
Teja Nidamanuru scored 41 not out off 34 balls.
Bas de Leede took 3 wickets for 74 runs.
Aryan Dutt took 2 wickets for 67 runs.
Post-Match Reflections: Jos Buttler expressed relief at the win and praised the partnership between Stokes and Woakes.
Scott Edwards acknowledged the recurring issues in the Netherlands' performance.
Ben Stokes was happy to contribute to the win and praised Chris Woakes as a genuine allrounder.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was held at Maharashtra Cricket Association Stadium, Pune.
England snapped their five-game losing streak.
